{"article_id":"P6vNF0N0EqECShVC","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Search For Answers In Boston :","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Why ?","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"How ?","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"Anyone Else ?","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"With the capture Friday night of Dzhokhar Tsarnaev , the 19-year-old surviving suspect in the bombings at the Boston Marathon , the story moves into a new phase","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"-","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"one","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"of trying to answer critical questions .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"Authorities hope to get many answers from Tsarnaev himself .","depth":4},{"id":9,"text":"As NPR 's Dina Temple-Raston said on All Things Considered ,","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"with the death earlier Friday of the suspect 's 26-year-old brother and alleged accomplice , Tamerlan Tsarnaev ,","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"investigators hope","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Dzhokhar will tell them","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"`` if there are other people involved","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"[ and ]","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"if perhaps there are other bombs elsewhere . ''","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"Key Developments :","depth":4},{"id":17,"text":"- Dzhokhar Tsarnaev , 19 , was captured Friday night","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"and is now hospitalized .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"He 's reported to be in serious condition ,","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"after presumably being injured during two gun fights with police .","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"He and his 26-year-old brother Tamerlan ,","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"who died after a gun battle with police earlier on Friday ,","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"are suspected of planting the bombs","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"that killed three people","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"and wounded more than 170 at this year 's Boston Marathon .","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"- The Tsarnaev brothers are also suspected in the shooting death of a MIT University police officer and the wounding of a transit officer .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"- Watertown , Mass. , the city of Boston and its suburbs are returning to normal","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"after a chaotic day","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"in which most people were told to shelter-in-place","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"while police searched for Dzhokhar Tsarnaev .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"Tsarnaev remained in a Boston-area hospital Saturday .","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Authorities say","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"he had multiple injuries ,","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"including gunshot wounds to his neck and leg .","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"Speaking at Fenway Park Saturday ,","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"Massachusetts Gov . Deval Patrick answered questions about Tsarnaev 's health","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"by saying","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"it is `` serious but stable ...","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"I think ,","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"not able to communicate yet . ''","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"Tsarnaev was involved in two gun battles Friday .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"An MIT University campus officer was killed late Thursday ,","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"and another police officer was wounded during a manhunt","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"that had Watertown , Mass. , and much of the Boston metropolitan area under lockdown most of Friday .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"The shooting of the officers followed the heavy toll from the marathon bombings","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"- three dead and more than 170 people wounded .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"As NPR 's Carrie Johnson reported Friday night ,","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"a Department of Justice official tells her","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"that Tsarnaev will not be read his Miranda rights for now .","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"`` We plan to invoke the public safety exception to Miranda","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"in order to question the suspect extensively about other potential explosive devices or accomplices","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"and to gain critical intelligence , ''","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"the official said .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"There are reports","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"that at least three people","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"who lived in New Bedford , Mass. ,","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"near where Dzhokhar Tsarnaev attended college ,","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"are being questioned .","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"Authorities also detained at least one man in the early hours of Friday","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"as they searched for Tsarnaev .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"We 'll be following the news .","depth":6},{"id":62,"text":"Come back to this post for the latest developments ,","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"and look for related news in other posts throughout the day .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"( Check this note for how we cover stories on days like this . )","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"Update at 5:10 p.m . ET .","depth":5},{"id":66,"text":"Suspect In 'Serious But Stable ' Condition ;","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"Sports Teams Try To Give Boston A Lift :","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"Massachusetts Gov . Deval Patrick describes Tsarnaev 's health Saturday as `` serious but stable ...","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"I think ,","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"not able to communicate yet . ''","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"The Boston Globe 's headline today is `` Let The Healing Begin . ''","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"The city 's sports teams tried to help ,","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"with the Bruins wearing police caps before their game ,","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"and the Celtics wearing yellow warm-up jerseys","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"that will be auctioned","depth":13},{"id":76,"text":"to raise money for bombing victims .","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"And","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"after the Red Sox held a commemorative ceremony ,","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"the team mounted a comeback win","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"that roused the crowd .","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"The Sox ' David Ortiz also won applause with his remarks ,","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"as he told the audience ,","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"`` This is our","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"( expletive )","depth":14},{"id":85,"text":"city ,","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"and nobody is going to dictate our freedom .","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"Stay strong . ''","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"Update at 2:20 p.m . ET .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"Dzhokhar Tsarnaev 's Injuries , And Possible Charges :","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"When he was apprehended in a residential area ,","depth":14},{"id":91,"text":"Dzhokhar Tsarnaev was suffering from gunshot wounds to his neck and leg ,","depth":14},{"id":92,"text":"says CBS correspondent John Miller ,","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"who reports","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"that `` this is a guy","depth":15},{"id":95,"text":"who was very weak at this point","depth":15},{"id":96,"text":"and probably","depth":15},{"id":97,"text":"- had he not been discovered -","depth":16},{"id":98,"text":"he might not have lived . ''","depth":16},{"id":99,"text":"The suspect remains in serious condition , as of the latest FBI update .","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"If he survives ,","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"Tsarnaev may face state murder charges as well as federal terrorism charges ,","depth":14},{"id":102,"text":"CNN reports ,","depth":15},{"id":103,"text":"citing a Justice Department source .","depth":15},{"id":104,"text":"Update at 10:50 a.m . ET .","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"Work At Crime Scenes May Be Slowed By Weather :","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"One of her law enforcement sources tells NPR 's Carrie Johnson","depth":13},{"id":107,"text":"that investigators have much work to do today at the various crime scenes in Watertown , Cambridge and Boston .","depth":13},{"id":108,"text":"They also caution","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"that the work may be slowed by weather in the area .","depth":14},{"id":110,"text":"There 's rain in today 's forecast .","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"Update at 9:40 a.m . ET .","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"FBI 's 2011 Interview Of Tamerlan Tsarnaev Likely To Raise Questions :","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"There was word Friday night ,","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"as we reported ,","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"that in 2011 the FBI interviewed Tamerlan Tsarnaev at the request of an unidentified foreign government .","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"As NPR 's Corey Flintoff reports on Weekend Edition Saturday ,","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"that `` could well have been Russia ,","depth":15},{"id":118,"text":"which has reason","depth":17},{"id":119,"text":"to fear terrorist attacks","depth":17},{"id":120,"text":"after a long history of turmoil in the North Caucasus . ''","depth":16},{"id":121,"text":"The Tsarnaev family 's ethnic roots trace back to Chechnya . ''","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"Late Friday , the FBI released a statement","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"that says , in part :","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"`` The FBI reviewed its records","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"and determined","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"that in early 2011 , a foreign government asked the FBI for information about Tamerlan Tsarnaev .","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"The request stated","depth":14},{"id":128,"text":"that it was based on information","depth":15},{"id":129,"text":"that he was a follower of radical Islam and a strong believer ,","depth":16},{"id":130,"text":"and that he had changed drastically since 2010","depth":17},{"id":131,"text":"as he prepared to leave the United States","depth":18},{"id":132,"text":"for travel to the country 's region","depth":19},{"id":133,"text":"to join unspecified underground groups . ``","depth":19},{"id":134,"text":"In response to this 2011 request , the FBI checked U.S. government databases and other information","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"to look for such things as derogatory telephone communications , possible use of online sites","depth":15},{"id":136,"text":"associated with the promotion of radical activity ,","depth":15},{"id":137,"text":"associations with other persons of interest , travel history and plans , and education history .","depth":14},{"id":138,"text":"The FBI also interviewed Tamerlan Tsarnaev and family members .","depth":12},{"id":139,"text":"The FBI did not find any terrorism activity , domestic or foreign ,","depth":13},{"id":140,"text":"and those results were provided to the foreign government in the summer of 2011 .","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"The FBI requested","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"but did not receive more specific or additional information from the foreign government . ''","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"Time magazine 's Swampland blog predicts","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"that the FBI 's handling of that 2011 request for information and subsequent interview of Tamerlan Tsarnaev will raise many questions from members of Congress .","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"Update at 9:05 a.m . ET .","depth":7},{"id":146,"text":"Homeowner 's Step Outside Led To Discovery Of Flapping Tarp , Pool Of Blood And The Fugitive :","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"The Watertown homeowner","depth":15},{"id":148,"text":"who tipped police off","depth":16},{"id":149,"text":"that Dzhokhar Tsarnaev might be hiding in a boat","depth":16},{"id":150,"text":"had stepped outside for a breath of fresh air Friday evening","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"after authorities said","depth":14},{"id":152,"text":"it was OK for residents to leave their homes ,","depth":14},{"id":153,"text":"the man 's stepson told CNN 's Piers Morgan .","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"Robert Duffy told CNN","depth":15},{"id":155,"text":"that his stepfather , David Henneberry , noticed something odd .","depth":15},{"id":156,"text":"The tarp over the boat","depth":18},{"id":157,"text":"stored in his backyard","depth":18},{"id":158,"text":"was flapping in the wind .","depth":17},{"id":159,"text":"It was the same tarp","depth":17},{"id":160,"text":"that had held firm through several blizzards over the winter .","depth":17},{"id":161,"text":"`` He got closer","depth":16},{"id":162,"text":"and realized","depth":18},{"id":163,"text":"that one of the retention straps had literally been cut","depth":19},{"id":164,"text":"- not chafed ,","depth":20},{"id":165,"text":"not broken or unhooked , ''","depth":20},{"id":166,"text":"Duffy told CNN .","depth":17},{"id":167,"text":"And Henneberry then saw blood on the tarp .","depth":15},{"id":168,"text":"He got up on a stepladder","depth":16},{"id":169,"text":"to look inside .","depth":16},{"id":170,"text":"`` He basically stuck his head under the tarp","depth":16},{"id":171,"text":"[ and ] noticed a pool of blood , ''","depth":16},{"id":172,"text":"Duffy said .","depth":15},{"id":173,"text":"Moments later ,","depth":16},{"id":174,"text":"according to Duffy ,","depth":16},{"id":175,"text":"Henneberry was calling 911 .","depth":15},{"id":176,"text":"Police were quickly on the scene .","depth":14},{"id":177,"text":"Within just a couple of hours , after a brief gunbattle and the arrival of a police negotiator , Tsarnaev was in custody .","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"Update at 8:45 a.m . ET .","depth":9},{"id":179,"text":"More On The `` Public Safety Exemption '' :","depth":11},{"id":180,"text":"NBC News writes :","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"`` The exemption can be invoked","depth":14},{"id":182,"text":"when information is needed","depth":15},{"id":183,"text":"to protect public safety .","depth":15},{"id":184,"text":"In this instance , the government believes","depth":14},{"id":185,"text":"it 's vital to find out","depth":15},{"id":186,"text":"if Tsarnaev planted any other explosives before his capture","depth":16},{"id":187,"text":"or whether others might have plotted with him to do so . ''","depth":16},{"id":188,"text":"Update at 8:20 a.m . ET .","depth":10},{"id":189,"text":"Also Hoping To Get Answers From Tamerlan Tsarnaev 's Wife :","depth":11},{"id":190,"text":"On Weekend Edition Saturday , NPR 's Tom Gjelten said","depth":12},{"id":191,"text":"authorities are also hoping","depth":13},{"id":192,"text":"that the wife of Tamerlan Tsarnaev will help answer critical questions .","depth":13},{"id":193,"text":"-- `` Dzhokar Tsarnaev ... In Serious Condition '' At Heavily Guarded Boston-Area Hospital . ''","depth":12},{"id":194,"text":"( CNN )","depth":12},{"id":195,"text":"-- `` Watertown Resident ,","depth":14},{"id":196,"text":"Who Lifted Boat 's Bloody Tarp ,","depth":14},{"id":197,"text":"Led To Capture . ''","depth":13},{"id":198,"text":"( WBUR ) -- `` Photos Force Suspects ' Move ,","depth":15},{"id":199,"text":"Breaking Bombing Case . ''","depth":15},{"id":200,"text":"( Boston Herald )","depth":14},{"id":201,"text":"-- `` Boston Bombing Suspects Wanted To Fit In ,","depth":16},{"id":202,"text":"Friends Say . ''","depth":16},{"id":203,"text":"( Reuters )","depth":15},{"id":204,"text":"-- `` Life In America Unraveled For Brothers . ''","depth":15},{"id":205,"text":"( The Wall Street Journal )","depth":15}],"relations":[{"parent":411,"left":209,"right":410,"relation":"topic","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":209,"left":0,"right":208,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":208,"left":1,"right":207,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":207,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":410,"left":220,"right":409,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":220,"left":212,"right":219,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":212,"left":4,"right":211,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":211,"left":5,"right":210,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":219,"left":8,"right":218,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":9,"right":217,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":